===Etymology===
{{PIE word|en|glōgʰs}}{{root|en|ine-pro|*pleh₁-}}
[[File:Complutensian Polyglot Bible - Genesis 1.1.png|thumb|The [[beginning#Noun|beginning]] of the {{w|Book of Genesis}} in the {{w|Complutensian Polyglot Bible}} (completed 1517), the [[first#Adjective|first]] [[printed#Adjective|printed]] polyglot ''(noun sense 1)'' of the [[entire]] [[Bible]]. On this [[page#Noun|page]], the [[text#Noun|text]] is in ''(above, left to right)'' [[Greek#Noun|Greek]], [[Latin#Noun|Latin]], and [[Hebrew#Noun|Hebrew]], with ''(below, left to right)'' the text of the {{w|Targum Onkelos}} in [[Aramaic#Noun|Aramaic]] with its own Latin [[translation]].]]

Borrowed from {{bor|en|grc-koi|πολύγλωττος|t=speaking many languages, multilingual}}, {{bor|en|grc-att|πολύγλωττος|t=many-tongued}}, alternative forms of {{der|en|grc|πολῠ́γλωσσος|t=speaking many languages, multilingual}}, from {{m|grc|πολῠ́ς|t=a lot of, many}} (ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*pleh₁-|t=to fill}}) + {{der|en|grc-att|γλῶττα}}, {{der|en|grc|γλῶσσᾰ|t=tongue; language}} (ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*glōgʰs|t=tip of corn}}) + {{m|grc|-ος|pos={{glossary|suffix}} forming o-grade action {{glossary|noun}}s}}.<ref name="OED">Compare {{R:OED Online|pos=adj.'' and ''n|id=147157|date=December 2020|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=adj.'' and ''n}}</ref> The English word is analysable as {{confix|en|poly|glot}}.

Noun sense 1 (“publication in several languages”) is probably derived from {{der|en|LL.|polyglottus}}, from {{der|en|grc-koi|πολύγλωττος}}: see above.<ref name="OED"/>

